<font color="#FF0000">MORNING ON THE RIVER</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec  6 17:07:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was out on the river again this morning.  The fog had just lifted from the water, which was running cold and clear.  My canoe paddle was cold in my hands, as it was aluminum and I have neglected to tape it.  I thought about what is happening with me, with the family, and our lives.  I also thought about others on this site, my Brothers of Choice, and how they were doing.  <br><br>
My wife was out on her run; my boy asleep in his room.  The beaver had enjoyed their morning's meal and retired.  The Chinook salmon had yet to come up-river, so except for me, the canoe and a few ducks, the river seemed empty and cold.  <br><br>
Sometimes our lives seem empty and cold, but it is an illusion.  Much is happening, just beneith the surface.  We can, through our actions and our inactions, influence these events.  But sometimes, we just need to drift in the current back home.
